28// The base class for all marking visitors (main and concurrent marking) but
29// also for e.g. the reference summarizer. It implements marking logic with
30// support for bytecode flushing, embedder tracing and weak references.
31//
32// Derived classes are expected to provide the following methods:
33// - CanUpdateValuesInHeap
34// - AddStrongReferenceForReferenceSummarizer
35// - AddWeakReferenceForReferenceSummarizer
36// - TryMark
37// - IsMarked
38// - MarkPointerTableEntry
39// - retaining_path_mode
40// - RecordSlot
41// - RecordRelocSlot
42//
43// These methods capture the difference between the different visitor
44// implementations. For example, the concurrent visitor has to use the locking
45// for string types that can be transitioned to other types on the main thread
46// concurrently. On the other hand, the reference summarizer is not supposed to
47// write into heap objects.
48template <typename ConcreteVisitor>
49class MarkingVisitorBase : public ConcurrentHeapVisitor<int, ConcreteVisitor> {
50 public:
51 MarkingVisitorBase(MarkingWorklists::Local* local_marking_worklists,
52 WeakObjects::Local* local_weak_objects, Heap* heap,
53 unsigned mark_compact_epoch,
54 base::EnumSet<CodeFlushMode> code_flush_mode,
55 bool trace_embedder_fields,
56 bool should_keep_ages_unchanged,
57 uint16_t code_flushing_increase)
58 : ConcurrentHeapVisitor<int, ConcreteVisitor>(heap->isolate()),
59 local_marking_worklists_(local_marking_worklists),
60 local_weak_objects_(local_weak_objects),
61 heap_(heap),
62 mark_compact_epoch_(mark_compact_epoch),
63 code_flush_mode_(code_flush_mode),
64 trace_embedder_fields_(trace_embedder_fields),
65 should_keep_ages_unchanged_(should_keep_ages_unchanged),
66 should_mark_shared_heap_(heap->isolate()->is_shared_space_isolate()),
67 code_flushing_increase_(code_flushing_increase),
68 isolate_in_background_(heap->isolate()->is_backgrounded())
69#ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
70 ,
71 external_pointer_table_(&heap->isolate()->external_pointer_table()),
72 shared_external_pointer_table_(
73 &heap->isolate()->shared_external_pointer_table()),
74 shared_external_pointer_space_(
75 heap->isolate()->shared_external_pointer_space()),
76 cpp_heap_pointer_table_(&heap->isolate()->cpp_heap_pointer_table())
77#endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
78#ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
79 ,
80 trusted_pointer_table_(&heap->isolate()->trusted_pointer_table())
81#endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
82 {
83 }

109 // ObjectVisitor overrides.
110 void VisitMapPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host) final {
111 Tagged<Map> map = host->map(ObjectVisitorWithCageBases::cage_base());
112 ProcessStrongHeapObject(host, host->map_slot(), map);
113 }
114 V8_INLINE void VisitPointer(Tagged<HeapObject> host, ObjectSlot p) final {
115 VisitPointersImpl(host, p, p + 1);

159 void SynchronizePageAccess(Tagged<HeapObject> heap_object) {
160#ifdef THREAD_SANITIZER
161 // This is needed because TSAN does not process the memory fence
162 // emitted after page initialization.
163 MemoryChunk::FromHeapObject(heap_object)->SynchronizedLoad();
164#endif
165 }
166
167 bool ShouldMarkObject(Tagged<HeapObject> object) const {
168 if (InReadOnlySpace(object)) return false;
169 if (should_mark_shared_heap_) return true;
170 return !InAnySharedSpace(object);
171 }
172
173 // Marks the object grey and pushes it on the marking work list.
174 V8_INLINE void MarkObject(Tagged<HeapObject> host, Tagged<HeapObject> obj);
175
176 V8_INLINE static constexpr bool ShouldVisitReadOnlyMapPointer() {
177 return false;
178 }
179
180 // Convenience method.
181 bool IsUnmarked(Tagged<HeapObject> obj) const {
182 return !concrete_visitor()->IsMarked(obj);
183 }

248// This is the common base class for main and concurrent full marking visitors.
249// Derived class are expected to provide the same methods as for
250// MarkingVisitorBase except for those defined in this class.
251template <typename ConcreteVisitor>
252class FullMarkingVisitorBase : public MarkingVisitorBase<ConcreteVisitor> {
253 public:
254 FullMarkingVisitorBase(MarkingWorklists::Local* local_marking_worklists,
255 WeakObjects::Local* local_weak_objects, Heap* heap,
256 unsigned mark_compact_epoch,
257 base::EnumSet<CodeFlushMode> code_flush_mode,
258 bool trace_embedder_fields,
259 bool should_keep_ages_unchanged,
260 uint16_t code_flushing_increase)
261 : MarkingVisitorBase<ConcreteVisitor>(
262 local_marking_worklists, local_weak_objects, heap,
263 mark_compact_epoch, code_flush_mode, trace_embedder_fields,
264 should_keep_ages_unchanged, code_flushing_increase) {}
265
266 V8_INLINE void AddStrongReferenceForReferenceSummarizer(
267 Tagged<HeapObject> host, Tagged<HeapObject> obj) {}
268
269 V8_INLINE void AddWeakReferenceForReferenceSummarizer(
270 Tagged<HeapObject> host, Tagged<HeapObject> obj) {}
271
272 constexpr bool CanUpdateValuesInHeap() { return true; }
273
274 bool TryMark(Tagged<HeapObject> obj) {
275 return MarkBit::From(obj).Set<AccessMode::ATOMIC>();
276 }
277 bool IsMarked(Tagged<HeapObject> obj) const {
278 return MarkBit::From(obj).Get<AccessMode::ATOMIC>();
279 }
280
281 void MarkPointerTableEntry(Tagged<HeapObject> obj, IndirectPointerSlot slot);
282};
